DATA

First lets see how the subfields compare

# reportedly available out of total
total_reportedly_available_data <- select_data %>%
    tabyl(subfield_groups, data_statement_indicates_that_data_are) %>%
  mutate("Percent" = Available/(Available + `No statement` + Unavailable)*100) %>%
  select(subfield_groups, Number = Available, Percent) %>%
  mutate(Real_Stage = "Reportedly Available")

total_reportedly_available_data$subfield_groups <- fct_relevel(total_reportedly_available_data$subfield_groups, c("Development", "Social", "Cognition", "Other"))

data_reportedly_available <- ggplot(total_reportedly_available_data, aes(y=Percent, fill = subfield_groups)) +
  geom_col(aes(x = subfield_groups)) +
  theme_classic() +
  scale_fill_manual(values=c("#EC407A","#42A5F5", "#FFCC33", "#00CC99"),
                     labels=c("Development",
                              "Social",
                              "Cognition",
                              "Other")) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim=c(0,100)) +
  easy_remove_legend() +
  easy_all_text_size(size = 8) + # change the size of the text
  easy_labs(x = "Subfield", y = "Percentage of Articles That Reported Having Open Data")

data_reportedly_available
